#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga"
msgstr "2. At Nālandā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Ukkacelasutta"
msgstr "14. At Ukkacelā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.14:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati ukkacelāyaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā tīre mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ aciraparinibbutesu sāriputtamoggallānesu."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjīs near Ukkacelā "
"on the bank of the Ganges river, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "
"It was not long after Sāriputta and Moggallāna had become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "sn47.14:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhusaṅghaparivuto ajjhokāse nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time the Buddha was sitting in the open, surrounded by the "
"Saṅgha of monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.164"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.14:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ anuviloketvā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were silent. He "
"addressed them:"

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.2"
msgid ""
"“api myāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā suññā viya khāyati parinibbutesu "
"sāriputtamoggallānesu."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, this assembly seems empty to me now that Sāriputta and "
"Moggallāna have become fully extinguished."

# The syntax of this sentence is obscure, see BB for variants. i take vaharanti to perform double duty as “live “and” stay”. Perhaps not grammatically justifiable, but it captures the sense.
msgctxt "sn47.14:2.3"
msgid ""
"Asuññā me, bhikkhave, parisā hoti, anapekkhā tassaṃ disāyaṃ hoti, yassaṃ "
"disāyaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"When Sāriputta and Moggallāna were alive, my assembly was never empty; I had "
"no concern for any region where they stayed."

#. VAR: hi → ye’pi (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: etapparamaṃyeva → etaparamaṃyeva (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.14:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ye hi te, bhikkhave, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, tesampi "
"bhagavantānaṃ etapparamaṃyeva sāvakayugaṃ ahosi—"
msgstr ""
"The Buddhas of the past or the future have pairs of chief disciples who are "
"no better than"

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.5"
msgid "seyyathāpi mayhaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā."
msgstr "Sāriputta and Moggallāna were to me."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, "
"tesampi bhagavantānaṃ etapparamaṃyeva sāvakayugaṃ bhavissati—seyyathāpi "
"mayhaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.7"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, bhikkhave, sāvakānaṃ, abbhutaṃ, bhikkhave, sāvakānaṃ."
msgstr "It’s an incredible and amazing quality of such disciples"

# garubhavaniya is dvanda, see AN 5.81 etc.
msgctxt "sn47.14:2.8"
msgid ""
"Satthu ca nāma sāsanakarā bhavissanti ovādappaṭikarā, catunnañca parisānaṃ "
"piyā bhavissanti manāpā garubhāvanīyā ca."
msgstr ""
"that they fulfill the Teacher’s instructions and follow his advice. And they’"
"re liked and approved, respected and admired by the four assemblies."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.9"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa, abbhutaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa."
msgstr "And it’s an incredible and amazing quality of the Realized One"

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.10"
msgid ""
"Evarūpepi nāma sāvakayuge parinibbute natthi tathāgatassa soko vā paridevo "
"vā."
msgstr ""
"that when such a pair of disciples becomes fully extinguished he does not "
"sorrow or lament."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.11"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kutettha, bhikkhave, labbhā. Yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ "
"palokadhammaṃ, taṃ vata mā palujjīti—"
msgstr ""
"How could it possibly be so that what is born, created, conditioned, and "
"liable to fall apart should not fall apart?"

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.12"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is not possible."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.13"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato ye mahantatarā "
"khandhā te palujjeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a large tree standing with heartwood, and the largest "
"branch fell off."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.14"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, mahato bhikkhusaṃghassa tiṭṭhato sāravato "
"sāriputtamoggallānā parinibbutā."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, in the great Saṅgha that stands with heartwood, Sāriputta "
"and Moggallāna have become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.15"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kutettha, bhikkhave, labbhā. Yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ "
"palokadhammaṃ, taṃ vata mā palujjīti—"
msgstr ""
"How could it possibly be so that what is born, created, conditioned, and "
"liable to fall apart should not fall apart?"

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.16"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is not possible."

msgctxt "sn47.14:2.17"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, attadīpā viharatha attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā "
"dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, be your own island, your own refuge, with no other refuge. "
"Let the teaching be your island and your refuge, with no other refuge."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.165"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.14:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, "
"dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant do this?"

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, "
"dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant is their own island, their own refuge, with no other "
"refuge. That’s how the teaching is their island and their refuge, with no "
"other refuge."

msgctxt "sn47.14:3.7"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, etarahi vā mamaccaye vā attadīpā viharissanti "
"attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā; tamatagge "
"mete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhavissanti ye keci sikkhākāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whether now or after I have passed, any who shall live as their own island, "
"their own refuge, with no other refuge; with the teaching as their island "
"and their refuge, with no other refuge—those mendicants of mine who want to "
"train shall be among the best of the best.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.14:3.8"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
